Ex-D.E. Shaw, Goldman Partners Plan China Fund, Reuters Says

-- B y   B e i   H u
-- 
2011-03-02T11:28:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/ex-d-e-shaw-goldman-partners-plan-china-fund-reuters-says.html
Meng Liang, a former partner of D.E.
Shaw & Co. , has quit from one the world’s largest hedge fund
houses to start a China-focused buyout fund with ex  Goldman
Sachs Group Inc . partner Kevin Zhang, Reuters  reported  today.  Meng and Zhang plan to raise $500 million for the fund,
Reuters quoted unidentified people as saying. Meng, previously
Greater China Chief Executive Officer of D.E. Shaw, and Zhang,
co-head Goldman Sachs’ Asian special situations group from 2005
to 2009, have received some capital commitments from Chinese
entrepreneurs, it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bei Hu in  Hong Kong  at 
 bhu5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andreea Papuc at 
 apapuc1@bloomberg.net  